For Valos, Cytel and IQVIA MBSM leadership receiving this invite: please forward this invite to all your MBSM associates

 

 

IDAR C&SP

 

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.

 

SPACE has been launched and more than 240 colleagues have been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy. 

 

Explorers can choose between the APAC/EU and US session for each occurrence. We look forward to your participation.

Description:
Hey everyone,

                             

Thanks for signing up for the tidytlg Beta release UAT!  We are very excited to work with you in the coming weeks!

 

Our goal is to test tidytlg on a variety of tables and listings using data and outputs across all areas.  We will kickoff the UAT team on Monday, October 11th with a mandatory half-day session to learn the package and create a demography table for one of your studies.  

 

After, we will have two half-day sessions and one optional session from Tuesday through Thursday where you can, with the support of the tidytlg development team, create unique and important tables for the area you support.

 

We have some meetings setup prior to this kickoff to ensure you have access to the R environment, the data you would like to use, and have the outputs you plan to programmed in hand.  Please attend these so we can jump directly into a tidytlg overview and programming on Monday.

 

If something comes up and you are unable to attend, please let us know as soon as you can to allow us time to get another colleague up to speed.

 

Thanks!

R Package Dev Team

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.

 

SPACE has been launched and more than 240 colleagues have been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy. 

 

Explorers can choose between the APAC/EU and US session for each occurrence. We look forward to your participation.

Description:
Hey everyone,

                             

Thanks for signing up for the tidytlg Beta release UAT!  We are very excited to work with you in the coming weeks!

 

Our goal is to test tidytlg on a variety of tables and listings using data and outputs across all areas.  We will kickoff the UAT team on Monday, October 11th with a mandatory half-day session to learn the package and create a demography table for one of your studies.  

 

After, we will have two half-day sessions and one optional session from Tuesday through Thursday where you can, with the support of the tidytlg development team, create unique and important tables for the area you support.

 

We have some meetings setup prior to this kickoff to ensure you have access to the R environment, the data you would like to use, and have the outputs you plan to programmed in hand.  Please attend these so we can jump directly into a tidytlg overview and programming on Monday.

 

If something comes up and you are unable to attend, please let us know as soon as you can to allow us time to get another colleague up to speed.

 

Thanks!

R Package Dev Team

For Valos, Cytel and IQVIA MBSM leadership receiving this invite: please forward this invite to all your MBSM associates

 

IDAR C&SP

 

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.
More than 240 colleagues have now been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy.

Description:
Hey everyone,

                             

Thanks for signing up for the tidytlg Beta release UAT!  We are very excited to work with you in the coming weeks!

 

Our goal is to test tidytlg on a variety of tables and listings using data and outputs across all areas.  We will kickoff the UAT team on Monday, October 11th with a mandatory half-day session to learn the package and create a demography table for one of your studies.  

 

After, we will have two half-day sessions and one optional session from Tuesday through Thursday where you can, with the support of the tidytlg development team, create unique and important tables for the area you support.

 

We have some meetings setup prior to this kickoff to ensure you have access to the R environment, the data you would like to use, and have the outputs you plan to programmed in hand.  Please attend these so we can jump directly into a tidytlg overview and programming on Monday.

 

If something comes up and you are unable to attend, please let us know as soon as you can to allow us time to get another colleague up to speed.

 

Thanks!

R Package Dev Team

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.

 

SPACE has been launched and more than 240 colleagues have been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy.

Description:
Dear colleagues,

 

We are very glad to invite you to join the 4th Data Science Making Impact seminar series held on 4 PM (Beijing Time), Oct. 28th. In this seminar we will talk about Machine Learning in general and have a deep dive in understanding of how ML/AI can facilitate clinical trial site selection. Hans Verstraete, Francisco Talamas from JRD Data Science, together with Hao Zhan from AP COE-TS Data Science will guide us through machine learning concept, cover its applications in pharma industry, and provide us a use case specifically for site selection. 

 

*  A Brief Introduction of Machine Learning – Hao Zhan

*  An AI / ML approach to site selection – Hans Verstraete & Francisco Talamas

*  Q&A

 







Francisco Talamas

Hans Verstraete

Hao Zhan

Director, JRD DS

Principal Scientist, JRD DS

Applied Machine Learning Scientist, AP CoE-TS

 

Looking forward to seeing you in the sharing sessions.  Please feel free to forward this invitation to anyone who might be interested. 

 

Let’s realize the potential of Data Science to reimagine our future together!

 

Sincerely,

 

 

Yang Cheng

Head of Data Science, AP CoE-TS

A separate meeting invitation is being sent to Non J&J Employees

 

For Valos, Cytel and IQVIA MBSM leadership receiving this invite: please forward this invite to all your MBSM associates

 

IDAR C&SP

 

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.
More than 240 colleagues have now been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy. 

 

Explorers can choose between the APAC/EU and US session for each occurrence. We look forward to your participation.

Description:
China R&D Learning | Training Sessions 



JCRD Health Care Compliance (HCC) Refresher Training

Dear Colleagues, 

Training is a critical component of our Health Care Compliance (HCC) Program that supports our ongoing commitment to doing business the right way. We have learned the core foundational principles of conducting business compliantly at J&J through enterprise HCC annual training. Building upon our existing HCC awareness and local risk-based training needs, JCRD HCC would offer a series of sharing sessions to strengthen the HCC rules and SOPs.

The first session will be focusing on Fee for Service, and HCP/GO Hospitality and Interaction. If you have interactions with HCPs & GOs or are undertaking projects that collaborate with academic institutions/hospitals, welcome to join us! You are welcome to ask any related questions during the Q&A session.

We look forward to having you there! 

Sincerely,

Your Janssen China R&D Training Team

Training Information

Date: Nov 16, 2021

Time:  14:30 - 15:30

Language:  Mandarin

Fang Xing

Lydia Liu

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.
More than 240 colleagues have now been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy. 

 

Explorers can choose between the APAC/EU and US session for each occurrence. We look forward to your participation.

C&SP Communications – SPACE Walk/Talk 

 

Dear SPACE Explorers,

 

Thank you for your participation and interactions in our SPACE sessions.

 

SPACE has been launched and more than 240 colleagues have been granted SPACE production access, so the need to go in more detail on SPACE items & Business Process updates related to SPACE is even bigger than before.

Note that the info provided in these communications is not covered in the standard SPACE Training.

 

On the SPACE portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  via the SPACE Walk & Talk tile <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM/SitePages/SPACE-Walk-%26-Talks.aspx>  you can take a look at 

*	the topics that are in a waiting list to be planned
*	the topics for the next SPACE Walk & Talk sessions
*	the topics that were covered in previous sessions
	(on the right hand side of the page there is a folder for each session holding the presentations and the recordings of the session)

 

You will have the opportunity to ask questions during the sessions but please also log your questions through our SPACE Q&A in Red Desk 2.0 <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/sites/PHM-GCSP-RND/DDA/RedDesk/Pages/default.aspx>  in advance.


We encourage you to visit our refreshed SPACE Portal <https://jnj.sharepoint.com/teams/SPACE_COMM>  to get familiar with SPACE. Please note that the SPACE Training assignments are prioritized based on the SPACE migration/start-up strategy. 

 

Explorers can choose between the APAC/EU and US session for each occurrence. We look forward to your participation.

*	When prompted, enter your Participant ID (Do NOT "just press # to continue").

ALL J&J USERS of Zoom for Business Meetings, in particular Meeting Hosts, are required to understand Zoom security options and to follow the J&J Usage Requirements for Zoom <https://mobility.jnj.com/zoom/zoom-usage-requirements-v2-1.pdf> . Use of Zoom for sharing any highly sensitive or personal health information should be avoided unless carefully following the Usage Requirements. Additionally, Zoom allows J&J meeting presenters to optionally record audio and other information shared during the meeting session. If a meeting presenter wishes to utilize the recording feature, the presenter should notify participants at the beginning of the meeting. If you do not consent to being recorded, please discuss your concerns with the meeting organizer either prior to or at the beginning of the meeting, or do not join the meeting. To ensure meeting confidentiality, please do NOT share meeting URLs and always confirm participants prior to the start of your meeting.
